# 5. やさしい言葉

Mizuki: *Stretch* I feel so much better after talking to you, MEIKO!
Mizuki: Now, let's go check out this new area. Wanna come with?
MEIKO: I'll pass.
Mizuki: What?!
Mizuki: But I don't know where it is! What if I get lost?! Can you live with that?!
MEIKO: You won't get lost. It's straight ahead this way.
Mizuki: That's still too vague! Can't you come with me?! Pretty please!
Mizuki: *Cry* MEIKO hates me.
Mizuki: She doesn't care if I get lost.
MEIKO: ...
MEIKO: *Sigh*
MEIKO: I'm going.
Mizuki: Aww, come on! You're really not coming with me?!
MEIKO: I just said I'm going...
Mizuki: Huh?
MEIKO: I'm leaving you behind if you don't hurry it up.
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: Hey! All you said was, “I'm going.” I thought that meant you were headed somewhere else!
Mizuki: I guess this means you're nicer than you let on, MEIKO.
MEIKO: And I guess this means you want to get left behind...
Mizuki: Whoa, hey! Wait for me! C'mon, let's go together♪
Mizuki: Cool...! So this is the new area...
Mizuki: But it's a lake... Right?
MEIKO: Yes, that's what it seems to be.
Mizuki: Hmm... It seems to go pretty far. Do you think there's something waiting for us on the other side?!
MEIKO: Who knows...?
Mizuki: Hey, can't you at least try to play along?!
MEIKO: I thought you were looking for Rin...
Mizuki: Oh, right! Let's see...
Mizuki: Hey, Rin! Miku!
Rin: Oh...
Miku: I didn't know you were here, Mizuki.
Mizuki: Yeah, I was so surprised when I heard the news! This place just sprang up overnight, huh?
Mizuki: Also, what are you two reading...?
Miku: Oh... A children's picture book. It came out of the lake.
Mizuki: What? Wait, out of the lake?
MEIKO: Mafuyu's feelings manifest themselves in this SEKAI. I'm sure this lake is connected somehow.
MEIKO: And despite being very clear, it's too deep to see the bottom. Her feelings may be hiding somewhere down there...
Mizuki: Mafuyu's feelings...?
Mizuki: Then, does this picture book also mean something?
Miku: Yes, I believe so.
Mizuki: I see...
Mizuki: By the way, what's it about? Can I read it with you guys?
Rin: Sure.
Mizuki: Thanks! Then, lemme squeeze in♪
Mizuki: Alright, let's have a look...
Mizuki: “Once upon a time, there was a little rabbit.”
Mizuki: “She lived a very happy life with her mommy rabbit and daddy rabbit.”
Mizuki: Hey, that's pretty cute... I kinda want to animate these rabbits now.
Miku: I'd like to see that as well.
Mizuki: Oh, then, maybe I'll do just that! I'll get Ena to do all of the illustrations.
Rin: Are you gonna keep reading?
Mizuki: Oh, right. Where were we?
Mizuki: “The little rabbit was a very nice girl.”
Mizuki: “She did her best to help others because seeing them smile made her very happy.”
Mizuki: “She also loved seeing her mommy and daddy smile, so she helped them as much as she could.”
Mizuki: “Whenever her mommy asked her to clean her room, she'd clean and clean and clean until it became spotless.”
Mizuki: “Whenever her daddy asked her to go buy something for him, she'd take her little basket and get whatever he needed as quickly as she could.”
Mizuki: “She also knew that studying lots and lots would make them proud. And so, she did.”
Mizuki: “As time went on, the little rabbit learned to do many different things.”
Mizuki: “But...”
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: “She tried so hard that she started getting tired.”
Mizuki: Wait, this sounds like...
Miku: ...
Mizuki: “Even so she kept trying and trying because she knew that's what would make everybody happy.”
Mizuki: “But then, she started to forget why she was working so hard and what she really wanted to do.”
Mizuki: “Still, even when she was in pain and so tired that she had very little energy to keep going, she kept doing what she could for others.”
Mizuki: “But trying and trying started to make her chest feel colder and colder. Until eventually, she couldn't keep going.”
Mizuki: Mafuyu...
Rin: Oh... Mizuki, look at the next page...
Mizuki: Huh?
Miku: “That was when the dog, hedgehog and cat came to save her.”
Mizuki: “The dog played warm-sounding music for her.”
Mizuki: “The hedgehog drew pictures of the rabbit going forward even when she was lost.”
Mizuki: “And the cat said nice things to her.”
Mizuki: Nice things...?
Mizuki: “The dog's music helped the rabbit open her eyes once more.”
Mizuki: “The hedgehog's pictures helped her feel hopeful about the future.”
Mizuki: “And the cat's words...”
Mizuki: “And the cat's words helped her escape the place where she had become trapped.”
Mizuki: “As sad and painful as it was to leave...”
Mizuki: “With the help of the others, the rabbit was able to protect what mattered most to her.”
Mizuki: “And then, the rabbit...”
Mizuki: Huh? That's it...?
Miku: Yes, the last pages are blank...
Mizuki: Right...
Mizuki: Haha. That's pretty cool... It's like an illustration of Mafuyu's current situation...
Mizuki: I guess it makes sense that we'd find this in Mafuyu's SEKAI.
Miku: Yes, I agree...
Miku: Which means... This story may be based on Mafuyu's feelings.
Mizuki: Mafuyu's feelings, huh...?
MEIKO: I'm glad this rabbit's friends were there for her when she really needed them...
MEIKO: I doubt she could've escaped without them.
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: (In this story, the dog used music, the hedgehog used art and the cat said nice things to her.)
Mizuki: (So, does this mean what I said really helped...?)
Mizuki: Thanks, MEIKO.
Mizuki: I'm gonna see what I can do about dealing with my own problems.
Mizuki: I mean, I can't let cottontail here hog all the glory.
MEIKO: Is that so?
MEIKO: Then, do your best.
Mizuki: I will!
